<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Portable Salt Meter Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Accuracy and Calibration:</strong> Ensuring consistent accuracy in readings remains a significant challenge. Portable salt meters require regular calibration to deliver reliable measurements, and any discrepancies can lead to misleading results.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Battery Life and Durability:</strong> Many portable salt meters struggle with battery longevity and durability, especially in harsh environmental conditions. Users often need to replace batteries frequently or deal with meters that malfunction in extreme temperatures or humidity.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Limited Awareness and Training:</strong> There is often a lack of awareness about the features and benefits of portable salt meters among potential users. Moreover, insufficient training can lead to improper usage, resulting in inaccurate readings and decreased user confidence.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Competition from Other Technologies:</strong> With the rapid advancement of technology, portable salt meters face competition from other sophisticated devices. These alternatives may offer multi-parameter measurements, which can be more attractive to users looking for comprehensive solutions.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Cost Constraints:</strong> The initial purchase cost of quality portable salt meters can be a barrier for small-scale users or industries with limited budgets. This pricing issue can hinder widespread adoption in niche markets.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Portable Salt Meter Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Technological Advancements:</strong> The integration of IoT technology with portable salt meters opens new possibilities for real-time data monitoring and remote management. Smart features can enhance user experience and drive demand.        </l